  "text": "In the following we consider haplotypes, which are phased markers, i.e., a set of 1, 2, or several ordered markers on the same chromosome. Haplotypes can be classified in classes. Classes can be formed by simple classification or by more sophisticated techniques such as cluster analysis [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . For the sake of discussion we will assume that haplotypes are composed of two markers with a putative QTL located at the middle, but our approach is general and conditional only on the existence of haplotype classes.",
